The paper presents deterministic algorithms for solving combinatorial optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on packing, matching, and dominating set problems suggests that the paper is more likely to belong to the first three categories, but the use of algorithms and complexity analysis may also make it relevant to the last two categories.
